The Western Cape High Court on Monday found former Western Cape police commissioner Arno Lamoer guilty of corruption. Lamoer alongside senior police officers brigadiers Darius van der Ross and Colin Govender had previously pleaded guilty in an agreement with the NPA. Lamoer and his co-accused aallegedly received cash and expensive gifts totaling R1.6 million from Cape Town businessman Saleem Dawjee. However, wife to Colin Govender, Sharon was on Monday acquitted on all charges. Lamoer was suspended back in 2015 when 109 charges related to corruption, racketeering and money laundering against him surfaced. -TNA Reporter